    "body": "Interestingly this slight variation on the above code does drop twice as expected:\n\n[playpen](http://is.gd/vXRySO)\n\n``` rust\nstruct A<'a>(&'a mut i32);\n\nimpl<'a> Drop for A<'a> {\n    fn drop(&mut self) {\n        *self.0 += 1;\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let mut cnt = 0;\n    for i in 0..2 {\n        let a; a = A(&mut cnt); // This was `let a = A(&mut cnt);` before\n        if i == 1 {\n            break\n        }\n        drop(a);\n    }\n    assert_eq!(cnt, 2);\n}\n```\n",
